<subSubSection id="C32229BC0B52866FFCDCFCC30DDF90D2" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B877A370B52866EFCDCFCC308B292F5" blockId="10.[824,1474,739,979]" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">
The single Indonesian isolate in the FSSC was further analysed using a two-gene phylogeny based on 
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B52866EFAC3FCED08609218" box="[1319,1367,807,830]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">rpb1</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B52866EFA76FCED08F59218" box="[1426,1474,807,830]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">rpb2</emphasis>
sequences. The analysis included a total of 2 461 characters (
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B52866EFCA4FCA80E58925F" box="[832,879,866,889]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">rpb1</emphasis>
854 and 
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B52866EFC2FFCA80ECD925F" box="[971,1018,866,889]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">rpb2</emphasis>
1607) from a total of 21 isolates representing the FSSC and two outgroup taxa (
<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B52866EFB4DFC4A081892B1" box="[1193,1327,896,919]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Nectriaceae" genus="Fusarium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="circinatum">
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B52866EFB4DFC4A081892B1" box="[1193,1327,896,919]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">
<collectionCodeEnum id="97533E150B52866EFB4DFC4A098F92B1" box="[1193,1208,896,919]" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">F</collectionCodeEnum>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B52866EFB26FC4A081892B1" box="[1218,1327,896,919]" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" rank="species" species="circinatum">circinatum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
NRRL 25331 and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B52866EFC80FC540EFB9293" box="[868,972,926,949]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Nectriaceae" genus="Fusarium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="fujikuroi">
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B52866EFC80FC540EFB9293" box="[868,972,926,949]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">
<collectionCodeEnum id="97533E150B52866EFC80FC540E449293" box="[868,883,926,949]" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">F</collectionCodeEnum>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B52866EFC9FFC540EFB9293" box="[891,972,926,949]" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" rank="species" species="fujikuroi">fujikuroi</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
NRRL 13566). Isolate InaCC 
<collectionCodeEnum id="97533E150B52866EFB1FFC54083F9293" box="[1275,1288,926,949]" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">
<collectionCode id="ED29E2F20B52866EFB1FFC54083F9293" box="[1275,1288,926,949]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15707" name="Field Museum of Natural History, Botany Department" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" type="Herbarium">F</collectionCode>
</collectionCodeEnum>
974 was identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B52866EFCBCFC760EFD92F5" box="[856,970,956,979]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ficidae" genus="Ficus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="longipes">
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B52866EFCBCFC760EFD92F5" box="[856,970,956,979]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">
<collectionCodeEnum id="97533E150B52866EFCBCFC760E5092F5" box="[856,871,956,979]" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">F</collectionCodeEnum>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B52866EFC95FC760EFD92F5" box="[881,970,956,979]" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" rank="species" species="longipes">longipes</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="130366B20B52866EFC3CFC76092092F5" box="[984,1047,956,979]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[113,145,1128,1146]" captionText="Fig. 4 Maximum likelihood tree inferred from the combined rpb1 and rpb2 sequence datasets of the Fusarium sambucinum species complex (FSSC) including one Indonesian isolate InaCC F974 (indicated in blue). Bootstrap support values and Bayesian posterior probabilities are given at each node. The tree is rooted to Fusarium circinatum (NRRL 25331) and Fusarium fujikuroi (NRRL 13566)." pageId="10" pageNumber="58">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) based on phylogenetic inference.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF472ABF0B52866EFF95F7C60CE0994D" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3565716" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3565716" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3565716/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" startId="10.[113,145,2060,2078]" targetBox="[151,1436,1078,2041]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph id="8B877A370B52866EFF95F7C60CE0994D" blockId="10.[113,1475,2060,2155]" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B52866EFF95F7C60D919938" bold="true" box="[113,166,2060,2078]" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">Fig. 5</emphasis>
Pathogenicity test of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B52866EFE97F7C60CF29938" box="[371,453,2060,2078]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Nectriaceae" genus="Fusarium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B52866EFE97F7C60CF29938" box="[371,453,2060,2078]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">Fusarium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. that belong to other species complexes. a. Plants before inoculation; b. wilting symptom caused by 
<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B52866EFA94F7C60DC6991E" authorityName="Maryani, L.Lombard, Kema &amp; Crous" authorityYear="2018" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Nectriaceae" genus="Fusarium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="odoratissimum">
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B52866EFA94F7C60DC6991E" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">Fusarium odoratissimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
InaCC F856, seven weeks after inoculation; c. control; d. positive control 
<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B52866EFC60F7EC096A991E" authorityName="Maryani, L.Lombard, Kema &amp; Crous" authorityYear="2018" box="[900,1117,2086,2104]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Nectriaceae" genus="Fusarium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="odoratissimum">
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B52866EFC60F7EC096A991E" box="[900,1117,2086,2104]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">Fusarium odoratissimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(InaCC F856); e. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B52866EFAE5F7EC08F5991E" box="[1281,1474,2086,2104]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Nectriaceae" genus="Fusarium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="proliferatum">
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B52866EFAE5F7EC08F5991E" box="[1281,1474,2086,2104]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">Fusarium proliferatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(InaCC F992); f. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B52866EFEE0F7F50CEE9977" box="[260,473,2111,2129]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Nectriaceae" genus="Fusarium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="desaboruense">
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B52866EFEE0F7F50CEE9977" box="[260,473,2111,2129]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">Fusarium desaboruense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(InaCC F950); g. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B52866EFD93F7F50E7E9977" box="[631,841,2111,2129]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Nectriaceae" genus="Fusarium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="lumajangense">
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B52866EFD93F7F50E7E9977" box="[631,841,2111,2129]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">Fusarium lumajangense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(InaCC F872 T); h. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B52866EFC14F7F509A69977" authorityName="Wollenw. &amp; Reinking" authorityYear="1925" box="[1008,1169,2111,2129]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Nectriaceae" genus="Fusarium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="longipes">
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B52866EFC14F7F509A69977" box="[1008,1169,2111,2129]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">Fusarium longipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(InaCC F974); i. FIESC (Indo161); j. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3801B40B52866EFF65F7930C64994D" box="[129,339,2137,2155]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Nectriaceae" genus="Fusarium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="10" pageNumber="58" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="lumajangense">
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B52866EFF65F7930C64994D" box="[129,339,2137,2155]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="58">Fusarium lumajangense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(InaCC F993).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B877A370B53866FFF95FF7A0C3991E1" blockId="11.[113,764,176,441]" box="[113,270,176,199]" pageId="11" pageNumber="59">
<heading id="D0CFCD5B0B53866FFF95FF7A0C3991E1" bold="true" box="[113,270,176,199]" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="11" pageNumber="59" reason="0">
<emphasis id="B94CA6250B53866FFF95FF7A0C3991E1" bold="true" box="[113,270,176,199]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="59">Pathogenicity</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B877A370B53866FFF95FF1F0C6B909F" blockId="11.[113,764,176,441]" pageId="11" pageNumber="59">
Representative isolates from each species complex were tested for their pathogenicity against banana variety Cavendish (
<figureCitation id="130366B20B53866FFF9CFEDA0D8E9001" box="[120,185,272,295]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[113,145,2060,2078]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1078,2041]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,1078,2041]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 5 Pathogenicity test of Fusarium spp. that belong to other species complexes. a. Plants before inoculation; b. wilting symptom caused by Fusarium odoratissimum InaCC F856, seven weeks after inoculation; c. control; d. positive control Fusarium odoratissimum (InaCC F856); e. Fusarium proliferatum (InaCC F992); f. Fusarium desaboruense (InaCC F950); g. Fusarium lumajangense (InaCC F872T); h. Fusarium longipes (InaCC F974); i. FIESC (Indo161); j. Fusarium lumajangense (InaCC F993)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3565716" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3565716/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="59">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Selected isolates included InaCC 
<collectionCodeEnum id="97533E150B53866FFDD4FEDA0F099001" box="[560,574,272,295]" pageId="11" pageNumber="59">
<collectionCode id="ED29E2F20B53866FFDD4FEDA0F099001" box="[560,574,272,295]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15707" name="Field Museum of Natural History, Botany Department" pageId="11" pageNumber="59" type="Herbarium">F</collectionCode>
</collectionCodeEnum>
872, InaCC 
<collectionCodeEnum id="97533E150B53866FFD5AFEDA0FFB9001" box="[702,716,272,295]" pageId="11" pageNumber="59">
<collectionCode id="ED29E2F20B53866FFD5AFEDA0FFB9001" box="[702,716,272,295]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15707" name="Field Museum of Natural History, Botany Department" pageId="11" pageNumber="59" type="Herbarium">F</collectionCode>
</collectionCodeEnum>
950, and InaCC 
<collectionCodeEnum id="97533E150B53866FFF09FEE70DCD9062" box="[237,250,301,324]" pageId="11" pageNumber="59">
<collectionCode id="ED29E2F20B53866FFF09FEE70DCD9062" box="[237,250,301,324]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15707" name="Field Museum of Natural History, Botany Department" pageId="11" pageNumber="59" type="Herbarium">F</collectionCode>
</collectionCodeEnum>
992 (FFSC), InaCC 
<collectionCodeEnum id="97533E150B53866FFE31FEE70CD59062" box="[469,482,301,324]" pageId="11" pageNumber="59">
<collectionCode id="ED29E2F20B53866FFE31FEE70CD59062" box="[469,482,301,324]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15707" name="Field Museum of Natural History, Botany Department" pageId="11" pageNumber="59" type="Herbarium">F</collectionCode>
</collectionCodeEnum>
962 (FIESC), InaCC 
<collectionCode id="ED29E2F20B53866FFD21FEE70FE59062" box="[709,722,301,324]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15707" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15707" name="Field Museum of Natural History, Botany Department" pageId="11" pageNumber="59" type="Herbarium">
<collectionCodeEnum id="97533E150B53866FFD21FEE70FE59062" box="[709,722,301,324]" pageId="11" pageNumber="59">F</collectionCodeEnum>
</collectionCode>
974 (FSSC). None of the isolates was able to cause any disease symptoms in the inoculated plants. All of the isolates tested caused only slight discoloration in the corm without any further disease development.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B877A370B53866FFF95FE170DDF90D2" blockId="11.[113,763,477,566]" box="[113,232,477,500]" pageId="11" pageNumber="59">
